The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval (PIR) with side information and storage constraints, which involves information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses caching schemes, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and computer networks (cs.NI). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.CR, followed by cs.DS, cs.CC, and cs.SI.
